cation's development from business analysis of existing enterprise processes and design to coding, deployment, integration with the existing ERP system, as well as mail and messaging services."]},{link:"/toddy",typeShort:"Marketplace, iOS",type:"Toddy Marketplace, iOS",title:"Toddy",image:"/_nuxt/img/work-toddy.fceda4e.jpg",imageLow:"data:image/jpeg;base64,",imageDetailed:"/_nuxt/img/work-toddy-detailed.50dead1.jpg",imageDetailedLow:"data:image/jpeg;base64,",description:["Toddy is an online marketplace for babysitters and young parents. We were responsible for the front-end and testing of this hybrid mobile application. The app was developed using Ionic and Angular frameworks that enabled quick development iterations and multiplatform deployment.","The native plugins enabled us to access all required smartphone features, such as push notifications, geolocation services, camera and others. Payments were implemented with the local Australian system Pin Payments."]},{link:"/pss",typeShort:"GIS, Web",type:"PSS Browser GIS, Web",title:"PSS Browser",image:"/_nuxt/img/work-pss.e3deb7d.jpg",imageLow:"data:image/jpeg;base64,",imageDetailed:"/_nuxt/img/work-pss-detailed.cd7fd92.jpg",imageDetailedLow:"data:image/jpeg;base64,",description:["This internal web application is used by an oil company to store and access data about the state of oil rigs and underwater pipelines. The app is built around a map view of the sea shelf with overlaid information about objects of interest. User can browse photos and videos of inspection results and view PDF documents in a browser.","The front-end of the project was created using Angular following Google Material Design guidelines. We used Node.js, Express.js and MongoDB for the backend. The app is hosted on Amazon AWS with static data stored on Amazon S3."]},{link:"/emf",typeShort:"SaaS, Web",type:"EmailMeForm SaaS, Web",title:"EmailMeForm",image:"/_nuxt/img/work-email.280dad6.jpg",imageLow:"data:image/jpeg;base64,",imageDetailed:"/_nuxt/img/work-email-detailed.4868f7d.jpg",imageDetailedLow:"data:image/jpeg;base64,",description:["EmailMeForm is an established high-load SaaS with several million users, who can create web forms and online surveys, integrating them into their websites and social networks.","In this project, our team jumped into the middle of the development and took charge of major back-end refactoring. Among our achievements were designing RESTful APIs from scratch, optimizing DB performance as well as integration with mass mailing service Mandrill and the Stripe payment system. We also implemented an automated UI testing framework."]},{link:"/segment",typeShort:"SaaS, Web",type:"Segment AI SaaS, Web",title:"Segment AI",image:"/_nuxt/img/work-segment.8de9a91.jpg",imageLow:"data:image/jpeg;base64,",imageDetailed:"/_nuxt/img/work-segment-detailed.074bca7.jpg",imageDetailedLow:"data:image/jpeg;base64,",description:["Segment AI is a service that helps to uncover segments hidings in user's lead data. Using data science and predictive modeling this service creates fine-grained analytics and improves marketing and sales alignment.","In just three months our team created an MVP of the application using PHP Laravel and React.js frameworks. This app features integrations with Google Account, Salesforce CRM, raw data conversion and interfacing with data analysis module written in Python."]},{link:"/strapping",typeShort:"OMS, Web",type:"Strapping Console OMS, Web",title:"Strapping",image:"/_nuxt/img/work-strapping.bd093ae.jpg",imageLow:"data:image/jpeg;base64,",imageDetailed:"/_nuxt/img/work-strapping-detailed.f20786d.jpg",imageDetailedLow:"data:image/jpeg;base64,",description:["Strapping provides styling services to its customers in exchange for a quarterly fee. Due to its subscription business model, the client required a customized order and inventory management console for internal use.","We created this custom single-page application according to the client's specification. We used MEAN (MongoDB, Express.js, Angular.js, Node.js) stack as an underlying technology for this project. The app features many integrations with third-party systems allowing the business manager to control all processes from a single place."]}]},serverRendered:!0}</script><script defer="" src="./Web Development Trends in 2018_files/manifest.d0eec973b8dfb64aba6f.js.download"></script><script defer="" src="./Web Development Trends in 2018_files/common.80ddd0fff1d0998abedb.js.download"></script><script defer="" src="./Web Development Trends in 2018_files/app.4fab47016b09a2900635.js.download"></script><!-- recaptcha placeholder --><div class="g-recaptcha hidden" data-callback="grecaptchaCallback" data-sitekey="6LeLYRsUAAAAAPp6UAqRjEkO6WgvXqyAWfuP8qmb" data-size="invisible"><div class="grecaptcha-badge" style="width: 256px; height: 60px; transition: right 0.3s ease; position: fixed; bottom: 14px; right: -186px; box-shadow: gray 0px 0px 5px;"><div class="grecaptcha-logo"><iframe src="./Web Development Trends in 2018_files/anchor.html" width="256" height="60" role="presentation" frameborder="0" scrolling="no" sandbox="allow-forms allow-popups allow-same-origin allow-scripts allow-top-navigation allow-modals allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox"></iframe></div><div class="grecaptcha-error"></div><textarea id="g-recaptcha-response" name="g-recaptcha-response" class="g-recaptcha-response" style="width: 250px; height: 40px; border: 1px solid #c1c1c1; margin: 10px 25px; padding: 0px; resize: none;  display: none; "></textarea></div></div><script>if(-1==navigator.userAgent.indexOf("Speed Insights")){var recaptchaSrc=document.createElement("script");recaptchaSrc.src="https://www.google.com/recaptcha/api.js",recaptchaSrc.async=!0,recaptchaSrc.defer=!0,document.head.appendChild(recaptchaSrc)}</script>
